def: The act or practice of itinerating; itinerancy.
A kiln to dry hops or malt; a cockle. Mortimer.
Adorned with, or wearing, a tiara.
Any of the players who meet in the final round of a tournamentin which the losers in any round do not play again.
An instrument formerly used at sea for taking the altitudes ofheavenly bodies, now superseded by the sextant; -- called also cross-staff. Brande & C.
Of or pertaining to Picts; resembling the Picts. "The Pictishpeer." Byron.
Separated from other bodies by means of nonconductors of heator electricity.
